stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Beanstalk
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] None
[Place of Birth] Columbia
[Date of Birth] Mar 10
[Race] Reproba
[Height] 155cm
[Infection Status]
Medical tests have confirmed that no infection is present.

[Physical Strength] Normal
[Mobility] Standard
[Physical Resilience] Normal
[Tactical Acumen] Excellent
[Combat Skill] Normal
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Normal

Professional Metal Crab breeder Beanstalk was born into a family of Columbian farmers. Although she has sent a variety of proposals to large corporations and business platforms, her attempts at courting their financial support have proven largely unfruitful, and she was advised to seek employment at Rhodes Island.
Having passed our examinations, she has been granted official operator status, and is now providing Rhodes Island with logistics and reconnaissance services

Imaging tests reveal clear, normal outlines of internal organs, and no abnormal shadows have been detected. Originium granules have not been detected in the circulatory system and there is no sign of infection. At this time, this operator is believed to be uninfected.

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 0%
Operator Beanstalk shows no signs of Originium infection.

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.12u/L
Operator Beanstalk rarely comes into contact with Originium. She is exceptionally healthy, as are her Metal Crabs.

Everyone passed their health examinations. We'll now hand out badges in commemoration of your success. Please step forward when you hear your name. That includes all Metal Crabs in attendance as well...
—Ptilopsis

Beanstalk made quite a scene on the day she reported to duty.
It was a blazing sunny day, and a Reproba girl drove a large truck right into the garage. She got off, opened the trunk on the back, and whistled. Then, her retinue of cheliped buddies all joyfully hopped off the truck one by one.
Beanstalk claims to be a professional breeder, and both the certificate she provided and this unforgettable sight have more than proven she is exactly who she says she is.

Each and every one of the Metal Crabs Beanstalk brought with her has its own name. Although only the breeder can truly tell them apart, as the Metal Crabs have become an inseparable part of our Logistics network, many of our operators made it a personal challenge to learn how to tell these little critters apart.
Beanstalk treats every one of her Metal Crabs as though they are family. Their names are Trey, Twista, B.I.G., Hammer, Ice Cube... and the youngest of the crabs, Peacake, who she keeps in a case she always carries around with her. As their breeder, not only is she able to tell them apart, she also knows the crabs' personalities and preferences. Every day, Beanstalk spends a large amount of time in their pen, preparing their nutritious fodder by hand as well as teaching them new tricks.
Having been tamed and domesticated, the Metal Crabs have become much gentler and more alert. The difference between them and their wild counterparts is night and day.

According to Beanstalk herself, even before she came to Rhodes Island, she had already been raising her Metal Crabs to handle logistical work.
This decision has to do with the unique characteristics of Metal Crabs. Their shells are hard, they have considerable strength, and the weight they can carry is substantial. At the same time, their body density is low, making them much lighter than they seem and allowing them to complete most of their tasks with relative haste.
With such qualities, Beanstalk thought the Metal Crabs would be well-suited to tasks such as mining, transportation, and certain special rescue or prospecting tasks. Her hunch wasn't far off, either. Rhodes Island conducted several tests specifically formulated for the crabs and subsequently issued a detailed evaluation report. Aside from the advantages their breeder previously postulated, the report also pointed out that the animals have potential in areas such as reconnaissance and frontline combat.
After reading the report, the astute breeder immediately went to work and started writing away. Then, after just a week, she had a new proposal for the Doctor about their future collaboration waiting on the desk. In the proposal, the Metal Crab breeder got straight to the point and simply emphasized her one condition: She would go on vanguard missions with her crabs, she would be the only one allowed to give them orders, and she would have the authority to order them to retreat if she deemed the situation too dangerous.
She was unwilling to compromise on this demand, and funding was of no concern to her as long as this was met.

Thanks to her cheerful, lively, and outgoing personality yet never-overboard enthusiasm, the Columbian farm girl became fast friends with much of Rhodes Island's personnel, including operators such as Vanilla, who came to her for breeding advice. Meeting a fellow breeder is no doubt exciting, especially in such a niche field, and this has both helped Beanstalk become more confident in her career and inspired new business ideas. Supposedly, she has started planning a new product called 'Beanstalk's Fine Pet Food...' I wish her good luck from the bottom of my heart.
As a farmland owner, Beanstalk's father is actually not very supportive of his daughter's entrepreneurial endeavors, or more specifically, he does not support his daughter's choice of breeding animal, Metal Crabs, as they are seen as peculiar and incapable of producing anything valuable to the older generation. This weighs rather heavily on Beanstalk. She has no qualms with taking over the family business, but she insists that breeding Metal Crabs is a worthwhile undertaking that will bear fruit.
She insists as such not just because she was once rescued by a small cast of wild Metal Crabs when she found herself in an accident out in the wilderness, but also because she saw a huge potential in these little critters. She truly believes that her hard work now will earn her everyone's respect in the future. Beanstalk had an argument with her family over this belief and chose to leave home, hoping to one day make a name for herself and be acknowledged by her family.
Although life has been difficult ever since, Beanstalk has never found herself dismayed by the difficulties she faced. On the contrary, it has only ever fueled her passion and enthusiasm.

Beanstalk never felt very apprehensive about having to interact with the Infected. When she first arrived, she didn't hesitate for long before she came to terms with Rhodes Island's sizable Infected population and signed her employee contract.
As the youngest country in Terra, Columbia is rapidly expanding and full of ambition. Each year, with nothing but their dreams, droves of young men come to its cities in seek of fame and fortune. At the same time, charmed by its slogans of equality and freedom, a great number of Infected gather at its doorsteps in hopes of reaping the rewards of the plentiful work available to them as explorers; earning a suitable amount of living space; and earning the equal treatment, perhaps even a tiny bit of respect, from the general populace.
Beanstalk was one such young woman born in Columbia, hungry for opportunity, so she was by no means unfamiliar with the Infected. She wasn't very bothered by the work environment here either, daunting as it may be. She understands that it isn't easy to chase after your dreams, and in a place like Columbia, there are just as many passionate dream chasers who pour into its cities as there are unsuccessful washouts who leave the cities behind. The Metal Crab breeder thought she had both what it takes and the dedication to make it, but her failures have forced her to admit that all successes also need that tiny bit of luck.
Now that Rhodes Island has finally given her a chance, the young lady has come to realize that, just perhaps, her luck has finally arrived.

An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

<color name=#ffffff>Beanstalk's personally coordinated casualwear / Gift Uncompleted. An off-white knitted sweater paired with light-green silk pajamas for a low-key aesthetic. When in the company of friends, comfort is the highest priority.</color>

modules.desc:
Operator Beanstalk has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude in the designation of tactical points for summoning reinforcements so as to secure leeway for deployment.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Vanguard Operator during field operations to exercise Tactician responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

'Beanstalk, that sales contractor you were in touch with finally sent their first draft of the ad copy!' 
'Nice! Lemme have a look!'
Thank you for choosing the 'All-You-Crabs-Eat' smart metal crab feeder! This device uses cutting-edge smart technology to solve any issue you may run into while raising metal crabs. Racked with worry that you can't tend to your crabs while away from home? Afraid that ordinary feeders could incubate harmful bacteria that will affect your crabs? Well, worry no more! The 'All-You-Crabs-Eat' offers your crabs a nutritionally balanced diet, all pre-portioned according to the latest science!
'Sounds good, but what's this 'cutting-edge smart technology'?'
'Oh, I asked Mayer to help with the computer interface stuff. In return, I lent her Peacake to help her develop a biomimetic intelligent partner.'
'I see...'
If you're using this device for the first time, please follow the illustrated instructions to assemble the feeder and food barrel, then use the touchscreen to complete your device's basic setup. The 'All-You-Crabs-Eat' offers three preset feeding schedules, and can support up to ten additional custom schedules. And if you can't bear to miss the wonder of even a single feeding session, order our camera now and enjoy a 20% discount!
'A camera? Whose idea was that?'
'I thought of it during training! The instructors stuck some tiny cameras on crabs for a while to assess their combat abilities. So I figured I'd add something similar as an upgrade for the feeder! Cute pet videos are all the rage on Columbia's intercity net, you know!'
Due to their omnivorous nature, we suggest setting the feeder to a single daily serving, with a serving size not exceeding 10% of the weight of your metal crab. The 'All-You-Crabs-Eat' supports freeze-dried feed, and requires no pre-crushing. We recommend using it with 'Beanstalk's Fine Metal Crab Feed,' launching alongside the feeder! With fifteen natural ingredients following a carefully developed formula, your crabs will be feasting like kings! Their pincers will grow stronger!
Usage instructions:
1. Do not feed children with this device.
2. Place the device on a level surface to avoid spillage.
'P.S. While setting up your feeding schedule, please remove your metal crab from the room. Some breeds are extremely intelligent, and may learn to use the feeder.'
'I-Is that really true?'
'Of course. That's how Peacake did. And if I'm not careful, she'll invite all her buddies over for a buffet.'

voice_lines.voiceText: Want my help? Hehe, I'll think about it if you give my buddies three days of luxury pet food! How about it, sounds like a deal, isn't... Hey, wait up! I'm just kidding! Don't go!
Outta the way, outta the way~ Beanstalk Breeding Center coming right through! Watch your feet! Careful not to step on any of us~

Doctor! Click is here at Rhodes Island? I can't believe you haven't ever told me! I'm a huge fan of her outdoorsy videos! She called Pea cute, and she even said she'll bring Pea along the next time she goes on a shoot!

There's been all these morons saying they'd go mining and then dug up a bunch of holes out in the wilderness. Fine, but how dare they make a mess of everyone's home! If I ever catch those bastards, I'm blowing a hole in their asses with my crossbow!

Doctor, I'm done with my breeding proposal. Take a look, will ya? Huh? The budget doesn't add up...? Tsk, he found out, huh? Oh, my bad! I probably got the numbers messed up somewhere! I'll get it fixed right away~

Before I came to Rhodes Island, I sent my resume to so many companies out there, and they all turned me down. Well, just look at how helpful my little buddies are now, both in the battlefield and in logistics. Those big shots only have themselves to blame. It's their loss!

You see, Pea may be the smallest of the Metal Crabs I brought with me, but she's also the brightest of the bunch! She's gonna be so amazing in the future~! My little buddies are nothing like the normal Metal Crabs out there. They're so smart! They won't be controlled by anyone out there so easily!

1, 2! 1, 2! Line up! Defense position, and block! Okay! All of you are doing amazing! Here's your reward. Eat up~! Let's switch it up now. Attac—Whoa, Doctor, how long've you been here? How come you're always so quiet when you walk?!

My old man doesn't really support me raising my little pals. He says they're useless, and that I'd be better off raising burdenbeasts. Hmph, I'm show him. I'll make it big with my buddies, and we'll see if he has anything to say then! Hey, Doctor, have you ever thought of investing in me? I guarantee you you'll be raking in lots of money!
Alright, focus! Doctor, you can't just space out while you're working. Take a look at what a good girl Pea is. Be more like her.
Hello, Doctor. My name's Beanstalk. Starting today, I'll be... Eh? What's in my case? Oh, this is Peacake. Here, Pea, say hi to the Doctor.
Aha! That was awesome! Did you see that, Pea?
Ehe, you're promoting us because of how well we did in the last operation, right?
Doctor, thanks for giving me and my buddies a chance to prove ourselves! I'll cut the formalities. We'll get even more amazing than this! You're in for a surprise!
It's our time to shine~
Alright! Everyone, do what I say!
Team Beanstalk, here we go!
Huh? Are these who we're up against?
Here you are.
All ready to go~
Go! Show them what we've got!
Let's go!
Hehe, you can't hit me~
Stop them!
I won't let you get past us!
You assholes! I won't let you hurt my buddies!
Hehe, you guys are no match for us~
Mission complete~! How's that? My buddies did great, huh?
Oh, some of them got through! Wait here, Doctor. I'll go after them!
*Sob*. It's okay, everyone. Don't cry. I'll beat those jackasses up next time!
I don't mind sleeping anywhere. Where's the breeding room, though?
Why'd you do that? Stop pulling my ribbon!
Hm? What's up? Wanna pet Pea?
Arknights.

Happy New Year, Doctor. For my New Year's wish, I want the Beanstalk Breeding Company to get founded this year without a hitch! If you'll do me just the tiniest favor, then I'll work even harder when I'm on the clock!
Yo~ Whatcha doing, Doctor?

Doctor, happy birthday! Given our unusual friendship, I've decided to give you a very precious present. Ta-dah—a robust little metal crabling, choice selection of the Beanstalk Breeding Company! Isn't he just adorable? Shh! You can't let anyone else know, or they'll all be hounding me for their own!

Rhodes Island dinner parties never fail to impress! But when do we get to hold a pet show here? We can compete to see whose pets know the most tricks, or just find out who's most popular. You want them to fight? Are you crazy, Doctor?! You think way too violent!
